## 📋 Additional Terms

### 1. Attribution Requirement
Any use of this software in academic, professional, or commercial projects must provide appropriate credit to the original author (Rajat Kumar) and include a link to the original repository: https://github.com/rajat-wyrm/jpmorgan-software-engineering-virtual-internship

### 2. Educational Purpose
This software is provided for educational purposes as part of the JPMorgan Chase Software Engineering Virtual Internship. It demonstrates concepts including:
- Real-time data processing with Python
- Interactive visualization with Perspective and D3.js
- Enterprise microservices with Spring Boot and Kafka
- REST API development and integration

### 3. No Warranty for Production Use
While this software is functional and tested, it is not intended for production use without further review, testing, and adaptation to specific requirements.

### 4. Contribution Guidelines
Contributions to this project are welcome. By contributing, you agree that your contributions will be licensed under the same MIT License.

### 5. Third-Party Dependencies
This project uses various third-party libraries and tools which are licensed under their respective open source licenses. These include but are not limited to:
- Python libraries (see requirements.txt)
- Node.js packages (see package.json files)
- Java dependencies (see pom.xml files)

